      "versionNonce": 1706332693,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773899783367,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Docker is a Software or tool, while Container is a running process just like VM, VM is also running\nprocess, these processes are different from our usual process that we run on our system. and running\nin the sence Docker is running with multi tenancy.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Docker is a Software or tool, while Container is a running process just like VM, VM is also running\nprocess, these processes are different from our usual process that we run on our system. and running\nin the sence Docker is running with multi tenancy.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "GYrsOj1CxFlx29V9HY6Xm",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1041.907295796342,
      "y": 65963.86037080291,
      "width": 253,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjb",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 65740821,
      "version": 5,
      "versionNonce": 933982965,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773898887289,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How are they different?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How are they different?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "WCV4g41QNN66MvyGoOwiI",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1078.801827046342,
      "y": 66001.98537080291,
      "width": 1023,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjc",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 845806357,
      "version": 190,
      "versionNonce": 742846971,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773898968553,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "these process have their own sub process, which is very common, interesting thing about these\nprocess and child process is they have multi tenant architecture.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "these process have their own sub process, which is very common, interesting thing about these\nprocess and child process is they have multi tenant architecture.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "myqGyBpFtD4bwAU6G3k2D",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1078.239327046342,
      "y": 66089.11818330291,
      "width": 396,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bjd",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 797503291,
      "version": 49,
      "versionNonce": 1416072667,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773898992659,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What do you mean by Multi tenancy ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What do you mean by Multi tenancy ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "XZa9yp768AzyZyy5htQl2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1101.270577046342,
      "y": 66128.45021455291,
      "width": 1133,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bje",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1010283893,
      "version": 1045,
      "versionNonce": 1790106641,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775656311829,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Suppose we are living in a building in a room on rent, if guest will come he needs to follow my\nrule as for him I am the owner, but if owner comes he can ask me to vacate the room or anything\naccording to his requirement, this same situation is with system also\nLike whatever process we are running, if someone is comming outsider we might deny to run certain\nthings because I am the root user. but our root permission whatever we have inside the container,\nthey will only be available within the container not outside this.\nUsually in Linux system there is only one root. but there are certain processes which allow us that\nin the entire system we can have our own space and within that we can have our own root. this root will\nmanage all the permissions related to this particular space without the interference of base root user.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Suppose we are living in a building in a room on rent, if guest will come he needs to follow my\nrule as for him I am the owner, but if owner comes he can ask me to vacate the room or anything\naccording to his requirement, this same situation is with system also\nLike whatever process we are running, if someone is comming outsider we might deny to run certain\nthings because I am the root user. but our root permission whatever we have inside the container,\nthey will only be available within the container not outside this.\nUsually in Linux system there is only one root. but there are certain processes which allow us that\nin the entire system we can have our own space and within that we can have our own root. this root will\nmanage all the permissions related to this particular space without the interference of base root user.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
