      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How do we remove file in linux?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How do we remove file in linux?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "BxXM2szHD2DoGIr_nEW5E",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1123.559639546342,
      "y": 70506.80177705291,
      "width": 1166,
      "height": 550,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk2",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1295153589,
      "version": 1109,
      "versionNonce": 1212975483,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773916648760,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "since here we are more concerned about images, the command is like\n\nremove file\ndocker rmi name of the image\ndocker rmi nginx -> it will remove the nginx image\ndocker rmi ubuntu:latest -> it will give erro due to containers are already running\n    with it.\n \ndocker images -> from here now nginx is removed\n\ndocker images gives detail of images, if we want any specific detail\n\ndocker images -q -> it will give all the image ids\n\nNow we will try to remove all the images in one go and see where it gives error and where \nit doesn't\n\ndocker rmi -f $(docker images -q) ->  to remove a image we either need name or id of image, it will remove\n            all the images on which containers are not running.\ndocker images -> not it will have only ubuntu:latest due to that container is running\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "since here we are more concerned about images, the command is like\n\nremove file\ndocker rmi name of the image\ndocker rmi nginx -> it will remove the nginx image\ndocker rmi ubuntu:latest -> it will give erro due to containers are already running\n    with it.\n \ndocker images -> from here now nginx is removed\n\ndocker images gives detail of images, if we want any specific detail\n\ndocker images -q -> it will give all the image ids\n\nNow we will try to remove all the images in one go and see where it gives error and where \nit doesn't\n\ndocker rmi -f $(docker images -q) ->  to remove a image we either need name or id of image, it will remove\n            all the images on which containers are not running.\ndocker images -> not it will have only ubuntu:latest due to that container is running\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "dFwZTzChZGOqBM7o0y1Cw",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1125.881905171342,
      "y": 71069.08693330291,
      "width": 495,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk3",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1358159829,
      "version": 62,
      "versionNonce": 482228501,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773916670788,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How we will deal with running containers? -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How we will deal with running containers? -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "sAm7C2S-iJEBRLBPRrjZb",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1179.514717671342,
      "y": 71108.62599580291,
      "width": 1089,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 727234517,
      "version": 222,
      "versionNonce": 1382550299,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773916773768,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "If there is a running container which is not in exit state, so the command is to put that container\ninto exit state is\n\ndocker stop container_id/container_name",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "If there is a running container which is not in exit state, so the command is to put that container\ninto exit state is\n\ndocker stop container_id/container_name",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "y6N6hCT1-eRYBAEV-QYwG",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1177.877998921342,
      "y": 71253.78224580291,
      "width": 1056,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk6",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 878295157,
      "version": 661,
      "versionNonce": 1151287189,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773920567388,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "containers are more like machines, after stoping also we can still reuse it. whenever we want\nwe can restart that.\n\ndocker start container_id \n\nwhat if we dont want shut down due to after shut down it is still holding on some memory, it is\nstill there as a process but the process is not active. So it has some space of mine, so we dont\nwant that space, So if we want to take away that space also.\n\ndocker kill container_id -> Now this running container will be in exit status.\n\ndocker ps -q -> it will list id of all running containers",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "containers are more like machines, after stoping also we can still reuse it. whenever we want\nwe can restart that.\n\ndocker start container_id \n\nwhat if we dont want shut down due to after shut down it is still holding on some memory, it is\nstill there as a process but the process is not active. So it has some space of mine, so we dont\nwant that space, So if we want to take away that space also.\n\ndocker kill container_id -> Now this running container will be in exit status.\n\ndocker ps -q -> it will list id of all running containers",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "2bvYYsp7C7EXGhDCECvZf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1106.026436421342,
      "y": 71567.85255830291,
      "width": 275,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 627634101,
      "version": 36,
      "versionNonce": 1652693973,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773917289456,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Pruning of a Container ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Pruning of a Container ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "pugboj0okyAORpfF1dDfa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1181.706123921342,
      "y": 71624.00490205291,
      "width": 1045,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk8",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 909328539,
      "version": 151,
      "versionNonce": 986347445,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773917461494,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker container prune -> it will delete all the containers that we have, It will prune all the\n            stopped or exited containers.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker container prune -> it will delete all the containers that we have, It will prune all the\n            stopped or exited containers.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "DySSyNAjOBflh25lehnDD",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1188.780342671342,
      "y": 71741.67287080291,
      "width": 1067,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bk9",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1537619925,
      "version": 572,
      "versionNonce": 724479483,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773917738059,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Pruning means if there are stopped or exited containers that we anyways dont need, why to keep \nthem and this can be with containers, this can be with images, this can be done with volumes,\nnetworks, so many things related to Docker.\n\nafter docker container pruner\ndocker ps -a -> we dont see any exited container\n\nbut if we have to remove a very specific container not from shutdown state, but we have to remove\nit forever then we do\n\ndocker rm container_id",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Pruning means if there are stopped or exited containers that we anyways dont need, why to keep \nthem and this can be with containers, this can be with images, this can be done with volumes,\nnetworks, so many things related to Docker.\n\nafter docker container pruner\ndocker ps -a -> we dont see any exited container\n\nbut if we have to remove a very specific container not from shutdown state, but we have to remove\nit forever then we do\n\ndocker rm container_id",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "fg0OViqC_HRTB96JbNUi9",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 977.6944051713419,
      "y": 72122.23537080291,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkA",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 560892891,
      "version": 97,
      "versionNonce": 98207797,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773924989063,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Containers are very fast and efficient way to spin up a VM. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Containers are very fast and efficient way to spin up a VM. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "91fDffCE5l49k42Q7t0--",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 978.3897176713419,
      "y": 72178.18068330291,
      "width": 990,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkB",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 502163675,
      "version": 117,
      "versionNonce": 1815746645,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773924989787,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Containarizing is not a proble in Industry now, because every one using Docker now a days.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Containarizing is not a proble in Industry now, because every one using Docker now a days.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "4P4pRUJyVbIWH6nNwaeG4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 977.6006551713419,
      "y": 72263.67287080291,
      "width": 1320,
      "height": 775,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkC",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1747258165,
      "version": 2834,
      "versionNonce": 420559381,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773920142833,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Containere are  not taking that much of RAM or any other hardware resource, that is not being consumed, So \nrather than spinning of one container people started launching multiple, And this always happens because\nwhen we have to scale our infra, scaling infra means we can catter more users. Faster scaling and efficient\nscaling means even more users. If we have to grow the user, ultimately we have to grow the number of\ncontainers as well. So prolem comes in the industry container management, there are multiple container now\nwe need to manage all , manage means in terms of how will multiple applications stay in multiple container\nSuppoer we have container runnning Application A, B, C, D, and now we want to change the containers that are\nrunning application B. This is one issue.\n\nIf we want to run multiple applications together, how will we separate them inside a single container Or \ninside a single machine which is running 2 containers, How will we separate them? that is another issue\n\nCommunication between two application or microservices that became a issue.\n\nNetworking and Security became the issue\n\nMostly when the containers are going down and coming up, then what is happening, which application is\ngoing down and which application is coming up?\nSo it is more like balancing between so many containers. So there are n containers and we are trying to \nbalance which one will come up and which one will be go down at what time.\nIt is more like there are n people, and they want to play different instrument, different instrument in \nour case is diff applications. and what we are trying to do over here as a developer or Devops engineer\nis who is controlling all of them or managing all of them or the another word over here is called as\norchestrating.\nFor Orchestration the tool in industry which is used is called as Kubernetes(K8S because 8 characters in between K & S).\nDocker also give solution for this like docker compose, another thing docker swam both of these have their\nown usecases, but we dont need to read them. Because industry is not using docker compose and docker swam.\nwe have better better version of this in form of K8S or also called as kubernetes. and we will see this later on.\n\nKubernetes is not only used for Docker container, it can be use for any hypervisor or any container. and it is \norchestrating containers.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Containere are  not taking that much of RAM or any other hardware resource, that is not being consumed, So \nrather than spinning of one container people started launching multiple, And this always happens because\nwhen we have to scale our infra, scaling infra means we can catter more users. Faster scaling and efficient\nscaling means even more users. If we have to grow the user, ultimately we have to grow the number of\ncontainers as well. So prolem comes in the industry container management, there are multiple container now\nwe need to manage all , manage means in terms of how will multiple applications stay in multiple container\nSuppoer we have container runnning Application A, B, C, D, and now we want to change the containers that are\nrunning application B. This is one issue.\n\nIf we want to run multiple applications together, how will we separate them inside a single container Or \ninside a single machine which is running 2 containers, How will we separate them? that is another issue\n\nCommunication between two application or microservices that became a issue.\n\nNetworking and Security became the issue\n\nMostly when the containers are going down and coming up, then what is happening, which application is\ngoing down and which application is coming up?\nSo it is more like balancing between so many containers. So there are n containers and we are trying to \nbalance which one will come up and which one will be go down at what time.\nIt is more like there are n people, and they want to play different instrument, different instrument in \nour case is diff applications. and what we are trying to do over here as a developer or Devops engineer\nis who is controlling all of them or managing all of them or the another word over here is called as\norchestrating.\nFor Orchestration the tool in industry which is used is called as Kubernetes(K8S because 8 characters in between K & S).\nDocker also give solution for this like docker compose, another thing docker swam both of these have their\nown usecases, but we dont need to read them. Because industry is not using docker compose and docker swam.\nwe have better better version of this in form of K8S or also called as kubernetes. and we will see this later on.\n\nKubernetes is not only used for Docker container, it can be use for any hypervisor or any container. and it is \norchestrating containers.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Nixbr7vTCqLaczFw-IQjW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 983.0928426713419,
      "y": 73114.67287080291,
      "width": 869,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkG",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 126610011,
      "version": 320,
      "versionNonce": 1813881019,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773925188197,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker images -> all the images\ndocker ps -> all the running containers\ndocker ps -q -> all the running containers id\n\ndocker kill $(docker ps -q) -> it will kill all the running containers\n\ndocker rmi $(docker ps -q) -> it will remove all the images that are not in use",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker images -> all the images\ndocker ps -> all the running containers\ndocker ps -q -> all the running containers id\n\ndocker kill $(docker ps -q) -> it will kill all the running containers\n\ndocker rmi $(docker ps -q) -> it will remove all the images that are not in use",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "IwWU5V85UHv_-J_AThPdA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 972.1358114213419,
      "y": 73366.20412080291,
      "width": 693,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1786906677,
      "version": 77,
      "versionNonce": 1582777141,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773925189980,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We can give name to our container also, we can't remember id ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We can give name to our container also, we can't remember id ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ID83qWMVsiwSkGggEMjHQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1021.7647176713419,
      "y": 73419.70412080291,
      "width": 495,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkI",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 642166363,
      "version": 79,
      "versionNonce": 704255995,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773925339866,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker run --name myserver -dit ubuntu:latest",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker run --name myserver -dit ubuntu:latest",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "qV8KrJIOgRIeo0uvrKCaJ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 967.1006551713419,
      "y": 73502.73927705291,
      "width": 539,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkK",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1905242261,
      "version": 55,
      "versionNonce": 488997045,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773925191852,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How to take background container to foreground ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How to take background container to foreground ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8R4tRZ-1wIdDshNFhpFWi",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1025.409248921342,
      "y": 73545.59865205291,
      "width": 1133,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1268557051,
      "version": 1076,
      "versionNonce": 1398295419,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773922110995,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "There are two ways to do this\n1. exec -> exec is not exactly the way to bring the container in foreground, but there is a trick\n        which we can use over here.\n2. attach -> attach is actually a command which is used to bring container in foreground\n\ndocker exec -it myserver bash -> bash is a command that will give us a terminal that will going to\n        run untill we will stop that. So exec is just a way using which we can go inside the container\nand run our command then again back in base shell. this only allow to execute 1 command but bash itself\nallow us to run multiple commands.\n\nctrl + p +q -> exit from the container without terminating\n\ndocker attach myserver -> this will get this container into foreground.\n\nusing exec we can run a command it will go inside and will come out, we don't even need to give -it we \njust need to give command.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "There are two ways to do this\n1. exec -> exec is not exactly the way to bring the container in foreground, but there is a trick\n        which we can use over here.\n2. attach -> attach is actually a command which is used to bring container in foreground\n\ndocker exec -it myserver bash -> bash is a command that will give us a terminal that will going to\n        run untill we will stop that. So exec is just a way using which we can go inside the container\nand run our command then again back in base shell. this only allow to execute 1 command but bash itself\nallow us to run multiple commands.\n\nctrl + p +q -> exit from the container without terminating\n\ndocker attach myserver -> this will get this container into foreground.\n\nusing exec we can run a command it will go inside and will come out, we don't even need to give -it we \njust need to give command.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "vqY4uSw-gCAFn1_-tzg0H",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 948.4365926713419,
      "y": 74015.82130830291,
      "width": 1144,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bkM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1689321237,
      "version": 236,
      "versionNonce": 704216795,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773922439582,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker logs -f myserver -> to see the logs\ndocker inspect myserver -> it gives metadata of the container, this will tell all the modifications done\n                    to make this container from any of the base image",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker logs -f myserver -> to see the logs\ndocker inspect myserver -> it gives metadata of the container, this will tell all the modifications done\n                    to make this container from any of the base image",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
