      "text": "To do this",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "To do this",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "KI9mXr0Svb0Rjz3G_8nDO",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1372.397530171342,
      "y": 77033.95412080291,
      "width": 1045,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bl8",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1470087509,
      "version": 491,
      "versionNonce": 1752634165,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773928442822,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. docker run -it -v /bin:/bin ubuntu:latest -> \n                    whatever sofware we have inside bin will be in /bin of \n                        container, a lazy way but this way can allow me to share all the\n                        S/W that we have in base to my container\n\n2 sudo netstat -tnlp -> now we can see we are able too access netstat as this is shared to\n                    container bin. and we have installed netstat in our base system bin folder.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. docker run -it -v /bin:/bin ubuntu:latest -> \n                    whatever sofware we have inside bin will be in /bin of \n                        container, a lazy way but this way can allow me to share all the\n                        S/W that we have in base to my container\n\n2 sudo netstat -tnlp -> now we can see we are able too access netstat as this is shared to\n                    container bin. and we have installed netstat in our base system bin folder.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "VrPXsUDUf1hRZQT3ZZ7_Z",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1336.893623921342,
      "y": 77298.64162080291,
      "width": 2530,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "blD",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 848835989,
      "version": 408,
      "versionNonce": 1376398075,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773929417588,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "task -> without writing a dockerfile, By going inside docker container we have to setup our Apache webserver, and we have to access it from our base system IP. For this we will use the base image of Ubuntu latest. How we will do? \n    1 launch a container Ubuntu \n    2 start Apache web server in this container \n    3 access this web server from base IP ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "task -> without writing a dockerfile, By going inside docker container we have to setup our Apache webserver, and we have to access it from our base system IP. For this we will use the base image of Ubuntu latest. How we will do? \n    1 launch a container Ubuntu \n    2 start Apache web server in this container \n    3 access this web server from base IP ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "LoKxQzCkFS0AAf6rOR-6i",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1451.6553426713417,
      "y": 77432.46974580291,
      "width": 1133,
      "height": 625,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "blH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1802923963,
      "version": 408,
      "versionNonce": 1548555829,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773931939628,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "docker run -it -p 80:80 ubuntu:latest -> this is a container if any request come on port 80 base system\n                                           will be redirected to this container port 80\n\ninside container\napt update\napt install apache2 -y\n\nservice apache2 start\n\nnow run http://publicIp:80\n\nOR\n\ndocker run -dit -p 8080:80 ubuntu:latest\nattach the container\ndocker exec -it <container_id> bash\nnow we are inside container\n\napt update\napt install apache2 -y\n\nservice apache2 start\n\nadd custom tcp for port 8081 in security groups\nnow run http://publicIp:8080",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docker run -it -p 80:80 ubuntu:latest -> this is a container if any request come on port 80 base system\n                                           will be redirected to this container port 80\n\ninside container\napt update\napt install apache2 -y\n\nservice apache2 start\n\nnow run http://publicIp:80\n\nOR\n\ndocker run -dit -p 8080:80 ubuntu:latest\nattach the container\ndocker exec -it <container_id> bash\nnow we are inside container\n\napt update\napt install apache2 -y\n\nservice apache2 start\n\nadd custom tcp for port 8081 in security groups\nnow run http://publicIp:8080",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Vm8viB-reK_gtfKC5ldHv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1244.7959676713417,
      "y": 78103.26662080291,
