    {
      "id": "HOXwJdYlQDArU5orT6Z6M",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1242.4717489213417,
      "y": 78200.47755830291,
      "width": 1166,
      "height": 400,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "blJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 897734613,
      "version": 1221,
      "versionNonce": 1895594427,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773932520582,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Lets say we have a Container now, we installed few things over here, web server and everything else, then\nwe want to package it as our own image and use this image to deploy more containers. how do we do this?\n\nOR \n\nLets say If we create an Image, but that image I want to send someone so that other person can make \ncontainers of it.\nContainers main use is , we have listen one application is working on my system but not working on someone\nelse system so to avoid this proble what we do now is that rather than deploying our application in a \nsystem we deploy it in a container. because container base is same for everyone. Because ultimately\nit is not running on our system, It is running inside container.\nSo what we will do\nWe have a container we will put our applicatin inside this, we will package this all as a image and after\npackagin it to a image we can now send this image to anywhere\nOther person just setup docker, he will load this image after loading the image, he will start the \ncontainer and container now has the application inside it so application is set.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Lets say we have a Container now, we installed few things over here, web server and everything else, then\nwe want to package it as our own image and use this image to deploy more containers. how do we do this?\n\nOR \n\nLets say If we create an Image, but that image I want to send someone so that other person can make \ncontainers of it.\nContainers main use is , we have listen one application is working on my system but not working on someone\nelse system so to avoid this proble what we do now is that rather than deploying our application in a \nsystem we deploy it in a container. because container base is same for everyone. Because ultimately\nit is not running on our system, It is running inside container.\nSo what we will do\nWe have a container we will put our applicatin inside this, we will package this all as a image and after\npackagin it to a image we can now send this image to anywhere\nOther person just setup docker, he will load this image after loading the image, he will start the \ncontainer and container now has the application inside it so application is set.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "n0njWP-4nmFMlSjI12EMr",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1325.7412801713417,
      "y": 78640.11818330291,
      "width": 1166,
      "height": 450,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "blM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1883351957,
      "version": 1306,
      "versionNonce": 634520027,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773933576913,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "diff between 5 commands of Docker \nsave, load, commit, export, import\n\nsave -> is used to conver image to tar file, now tar file can be mailed anywhere, can be whatsapp \n        or can be sent anywhere, saving img -> tar, image already has metadata in it.\n\nload -> reverse of save, have tar file, will load image from the tar file and have a image\ncommit -> from a running container, if we want to crate image from this\n        Example lets say in our Apache server practicle we have set everything but forgot to \n                port forwarding, so what we will do , we will come out of this \n                ctrl + p + q then commit the container now we have image, we will create a new container\n                with this image with port forwarding.\n\nexport -> it will crate tar file of our running container, container -> .tar, here running state becomes\n            the tar file, in save we have all metadata of image\nimport -> import tar will give the image, image can launch same container that we have exported, but there\n        will be no meta data. It will look like we have setup a fresh base container with the loss of \n        metadata. (tar->img) with the loss of metadata",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "diff between 5 commands of Docker \nsave, load, commit, export, import\n\nsave -> is used to conver image to tar file, now tar file can be mailed anywhere, can be whatsapp \n        or can be sent anywhere, saving img -> tar, image already has metadata in it.\n\nload -> reverse of save, have tar file, will load image from the tar file and have a image\ncommit -> from a running container, if we want to crate image from this\n        Example lets say in our Apache server practicle we have set everything but forgot to \n                port forwarding, so what we will do , we will come out of this \n                ctrl + p + q then commit the container now we have image, we will create a new container\n                with this image with port forwarding.\n\nexport -> it will crate tar file of our running container, container -> .tar, here running state becomes\n            the tar file, in save we have all metadata of image\nimport -> import tar will give the image, image can launch same container that we have exported, but there\n        will be no meta data. It will look like we have setup a fresh base container with the loss of \n        metadata. (tar->img) with the loss of metadata",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
