      "seed": 1074905197,
      "version": 753,
      "versionNonce": 398604579,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774017529291,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "lets say we have a ubuntu container running in background -dlt\nthen we are installing python server\nexec install ws\nlets say one more exec that will setup post and firewall \nother exec command this will pull website code from Github\n\nand all these things are linux commands, all these things can be scripted, ultimate output is we will\nget a container\n\nFrom this container we can run another command as a part of this script only that will make a image\nNow we know the command to make a image from a container. So we have a image also\n\ndockerfile is a way of creating a image with all these modifications.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "lets say we have a ubuntu container running in background -dlt\nthen we are installing python server\nexec install ws\nlets say one more exec that will setup post and firewall \nother exec command this will pull website code from Github\n\nand all these things are linux commands, all these things can be scripted, ultimate output is we will\nget a container\n\nFrom this container we can run another command as a part of this script only that will make a image\nNow we know the command to make a image from a container. So we have a image also\n\ndockerfile is a way of creating a image with all these modifications.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Q5dXk6RyMxYqBZmI5Glt9",
      "type": "text",
