      "seed": 339926723,
      "version": 34,
      "versionNonce": 1104576003,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774019249394,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Why Single dockerfile only ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why Single dockerfile only ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "RT_kSmWnP3bKXUgMTlnh7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1392.5420614213417,
      "y": 82058.59865205291,
      "width": 1133,
      "height": 600,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "blh",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1394284867,
      "version": 1344,
      "versionNonce": 890218029,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774020217387,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "due to docker will recognize it by direct filename compulsorily has to be dockerfile. So obviously\nin a single location we can't put multiple file with same name.\n\nmkdir p1\ncd p1\nvi dockerfile -> it should be key and parameter\n                 1 FROM  ubuntu:latest  \n                            from basically takes the input of what base image we want to use, If we are\n                            not having image it will pull, if we are having that, it is going to use\n                            that, this we can write small or cap also , since we want to distinguise\n                            it from the command good to write it is all caps. Just a convention not\n                            a rule.\n                 2 RUN touch f1\n\n                 save and exit this file :wq\n\nNow run this dockerfile, to run the dockerfile or to create a image from this what we have to do is\nrun the docker command\ndocker build -t myubuntu . -> . means location of docker file which is current location\n                                myubuntu is image name, if the dockerfile file is in other\n                                location that we can give .\n\ndocker run -it myubuntu -> run the conatainer\nnow do ls inside container we will see f1 is there.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "due to docker will recognize it by direct filename compulsorily has to be dockerfile. So obviously\nin a single location we can't put multiple file with same name.\n\nmkdir p1\ncd p1\nvi dockerfile -> it should be key and parameter\n                 1 FROM  ubuntu:latest  \n                            from basically takes the input of what base image we want to use, If we are\n                            not having image it will pull, if we are having that, it is going to use\n                            that, this we can write small or cap also , since we want to distinguise\n                            it from the command good to write it is all caps. Just a convention not\n                            a rule.\n                 2 RUN touch f1\n\n                 save and exit this file :wq\n\nNow run this dockerfile, to run the dockerfile or to create a image from this what we have to do is\nrun the docker command\ndocker build -t myubuntu . -> . means location of docker file which is current location\n                                myubuntu is image name, if the dockerfile file is in other\n                                location that we can give .\n\ndocker run -it myubuntu -> run the conatainer\nnow do ls inside container we will see f1 is there.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
