      "locked": false,
      "text": "How dockerfile works?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How dockerfile works?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "WlBzwtjQH13ENkpi3Nzhe",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1503.6670614213417,
      "y": 84477.01792288624,
      "width": 1122,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "blq",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 336533187,
      "version": 1886,
      "versionNonce": 218374381,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774029958521,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "when we run the dockerfile or when we run the build command, what happen first of all our\nimage is get pulled from hub or whereever it is our repo. So image get pulled from this image\nthey run a container, this container will be package as a image and passed to next RUN commands\nand so on.\nAll the dockerfile commands knows one thing that they have to get a image and then run a container\nto work on it.\n\nIn summary every command of dockerfile get an image, then container is made to run that command\nand then again package it as a image and pass to next command and so on\nAll of command same purpose get a image, run the container on that image, do whatever is told to\ndo and repack it to a image.\nSo lets say final we have a ENTRYPOINT here, this will get an image, it will run container do whatever\nis told to do here, after doing it, it will repack it to a image and that is why the final output \nthat we get of a long dockerfile is a image.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "when we run the dockerfile or when we run the build command, what happen first of all our\nimage is get pulled from hub or whereever it is our repo. So image get pulled from this image\nthey run a container, this container will be package as a image and passed to next RUN commands\nand so on.\nAll the dockerfile commands knows one thing that they have to get a image and then run a container\nto work on it.\n\nIn summary every command of dockerfile get an image, then container is made to run that command\nand then again package it as a image and pass to next command and so on\nAll of command same purpose get a image, run the container on that image, do whatever is told to\ndo and repack it to a image.\nSo lets say final we have a ENTRYPOINT here, this will get an image, it will run container do whatever\nis told to do here, after doing it, it will repack it to a image and that is why the final output \nthat we get of a long dockerfile is a image.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
